1 (3) May, prior to taking the person before a judicial official, take the person
2 arrested to some other place if the person so requests.
3 (4) May, prior to taking the person before a judicial official, take the person
4 arrested to some other place if such action is reasonably necessary for the
5 purpose of having that person identified.
6 (5) Must without unnecessary delay advise the person arrested of his right to
7 communicate with counsel and friends and must allow him reasonable time
8 and reasonable opportunity to do so.
9 (6) Must make available to the State on a timely basis all materials and
10 information acquired in the course of all felony investigations. This
11 responsibility is a continuing affirmative duty."
