18 report and risk assessment, if available, for the defendant and shall consider the criminal history
19 when setting conditions of pretrial release. After setting conditions of pretrial release, the judge
20 shall return the report to the providing agency or department. No judge shall unreasonably delay
21 the determination of conditions of pretrial release for the purpose of reviewing the defendant's
22 criminal history report. Notwithstanding the provisions of this subsection, a magistrate or the
23 clerk of superior court may set the conditions of pretrial release at any time if the new offense is
24 a violation of Chapter 20 of the General Statutes, other than a violation of G.S. 20-138.1,
