1 to appear to answer one or more of the charges to which the conditions apply, the judicial official
2 shall at a minimum impose the conditions of pretrial release that are recommended in any order
3 for the arrest of the defendant that was issued for the defendant's most recent failure to appear. If
4 no conditions are recommended in that order for arrest, the judicial official shall require the
5 execution of a secured appearance bond in an amount at least double the amount of the most
6 recent previous secured or unsecured bond for the charges or, if no bond has yet been required
7 for the charges, in the amount of at least one thousand dollars ($1,000). The judicial official shall
8 also impose such restrictions on the travel, associations, conduct, or place of abode of the
9 defendant as will assure that the defendant will not again fail to appear. The judicial official shall
10 indicate on the release order that the defendant was arrested or surrendered after failing to appear
11 as required under a prior release order. If the information available to the judicial official
12 indicates that the defendant has failed on two or more prior occasions to appear to answer the
13 charges, the judicial official shall indicate that fact on the release order.
14 (d2) When Except for a defendant charged with a violent offense, when conditions of
15 pretrial release are being determined for a defendant who is charged with a felony offense and
16 the defendant is currently on probation for a prior offense, a judicial official shall determine
17 whether the defendant poses a danger to the public prior to imposing conditions of pretrial release
18 and must record that determination in writing. This subsection shall apply to any judicial official
19 authorized to determine or review the defendant's eligibility for release under any proceeding
20 authorized by this Chapter. After making a determination pursuant to this subsection, the judicial
21 official shall impose the following conditions:
22 (1) If the judicial official determines that the defendant poses a danger to the
23 public, the judicial official must impose condition (4) or (5) in subsection (a)
24 of this section instead of condition (1), (2), (2) or (3).
25 (2) If the judicial official finds that the defendant does not pose a danger to the
26 public, then conditions of pretrial release shall be imposed as otherwise
27 provided in this Article.
28 (3) If there is insufficient information to determine whether the defendant poses
29 a danger to the public, then the defendant shall be retained in custody until a
30 determination of pretrial release conditions is made pursuant to this
31 subdivision. The judicial official that orders that the defendant be retained in
32 custody shall set forth, in writing, the following at the time that the order is
33 entered:
34 a. The defendant is being held pursuant to this subdivision.
35 b. The basis for the judicial official's decision that additional information
36 is needed to determine whether the defendant poses a danger to the
37 public and the nature of the necessary information.
38 c. A date, within 72 hours or 96 hours if the courthouse is closed for
39 transactions for a period longer than 72 hours, of the time of arrest,
40 when the defendant shall be brought before a judge for a first
41 appearance pursuant to Article 29 of this Chapter. If the necessary
42 information is provided to the court at any time prior to the first
43 appearance, the first available judicial official shall set the conditions
44 of pretrial release. The judge who reviews the defendant's eligibility
45 for release at the first appearance shall determine the conditions of
46 pretrial release as provided in this Article.
47 (d3) When conditions of pretrial release are being determined for a defendant who is
48 charged with an offense and the defendant is currently on pretrial release for a prior offense, the
49 judicial official may require the execution of a secured appearance bond in an amount at least
50 double the amount of the most recent previous secured or unsecured bond for the charges or, if
