27 SECTION 1.(g) No later than the effective date of subsections (a) through (e) of this
28 section, each judicial district that does not already have the capability of imposing house arrest
29 with electronic monitoring under G.S. 15A-534(a)(5) shall enter into a Memorandum of
30 Agreement with a qualified vendor to provide such services. A defendant released with the
31 condition of house arrest with electronic monitoring shall be responsible for paying for the
32 services provided by the qualified vendor.
33 SECTION 1.(h) No later than the effective date of subsections (a) through (e) of this
34 section, the Administrative Office of the Courts shall provide a method for judicial officials to
35 determine if a defendant has a prior order of involuntary commitment, pursuant to Article 5 of
36 Chapter 122C of the General Statutes, for purposes of complying with subsections (a) through
