11 DIRECT THE COLLABORATORY TO STUDY MENTAL HEALTH AND THE
12 JUSTICE SYSTEM
13 SECTION 4. The North Carolina Collaboratory (Collaboratory) shall study the
14 following:
15 (1) The intersection of mental health in the justice system for both adults and
16 juveniles in North Carolina, including initial response, mental health
17 evaluation, inpatient and outpatient involuntary commitment, incarceration,
18 post-release monitoring and treatment, and any other items the Collaboratory
19 deems relevant.
20 (2) The availability of house arrest as a condition of pretrial release in each county
21 or judicial district.
22 (3) Methods of execution other than those currently authorized by State law.
23 This study may include the issuance of one or more research awards to provide, as
24 necessary, planning grants for a preliminary investigation to (i) identify, obtain, and analyze
25 existing data, (ii) identify other critical data that could be acquired and analyzed, (iii) identify
26 appropriate stakeholder groups for engagement, (iv) develop a holistic and longer-term research
27 team and plan with a formal scope of work, time line, and deliverables, and (v) any other items
28 the Collaboratory deems relevant. The Collaboratory may also utilize these preliminary findings
29 to fund one or more awards for additional research to support this study.
30 Any unit of State or local government that receives a written request from the
31 Collaboratory, including an electronically transmitted request, shall cooperate and assist the
32 Collaboratory with this study by providing full access to personnel and data within 30 calendar
33 days of the request. Any information or data received that is confidential or not public record
34 shall remain confidential, shall be withheld from public inspection, shall be used only for the
35 purposes this study, and may not be publicly disclosed except as deidentified, aggregated
36 information or data.
37 The Collaboratory shall provide a preliminary report of its findings to the Joint
38 Legislative Commission on Governmental Operations no later than April 1, 2026, and a final
39 report of its findings, including any policy or funding recommendations, no later than March 1,
40 2027.
41 Notwithstanding any provision of law to the contrary, of the funds appropriated to
42 The University of North Carolina (Budget Code 16020) for the North Carolina Policy
43 Collaboratory (Collaboratory) for the purposes described in Item 188 on Page B-56 of the
44 Committee Report referenced in Section 43.2 of S.L. 2021-180, the Collaboratory shall reallocate
45 up to one million dollars ($1,000,000) for the study required under this section, including
46 consultants or faculty, staff, or students affiliated with institutions of higher education.
47
