22 "§ 15-188. Manner and place of execution.
23 (a) In accordance with G.S. 15-187, Unless subsection (b) of this section applies, the
24 mode of executing a death sentence must in every case be by administering to the convict or felon
25 an intravenous injection of a substance or substances in a lethal quantity sufficient to cause death
26 and until the person is dead, and that procedure shall be determined by the Secretary of the
27 Department of Adult Correction, who shall ensure compliance with the federal and State
28 constitutions; and when any person, convict or felon shall be sentenced by any court of the State
29 having competent jurisdiction to be so executed, the punishment shall only be inflicted within a
